### Bold POS API – Test Trace
### Base: http://localhost:3000/api/v1
### Run with VSCode REST Client

@base = http://localhost:3000/api/v1
@token = 

### 1. AUTH – Login
# @name login
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "+200100000000",
  "password": "Bold1234"
}

### Set token manually: @token = <access_token from login>

### 2. PRODUCTS – Search by barcode
GET {{base}}/products/search?q=6223001000011
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 3. PRODUCTS – Create
POST {{base}}/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name_en": "Test Polo",
  "sku": "BOLD-TEST-001-M-RED",
  "barcode_ean13": "6223001999999",
  "barcode_internal": "BOLD-TEST-001-M-RED",
  "size": "M",
  "color": "Red",
  "cost_price": 120,
  "brand": "Bold"
}

### 4. PRICING – Calculate
POST {{base}}/pricing/calculate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "variant_id": "<paste-variant-id-from-search>"
}

### 5. INVENTORY – Lookup across branches
GET {{base}}/inventory/lookup?variant_id=<variant-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. CUSTOMERS – List
GET {{base}}/customers?q=0101
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. CUSTOMERS – Loyalty check
GET {{base}}/customers/loyalty?phone=01011111111
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. CUSTOMERS – Create
POST {{base}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "عميل اختبار",
  "phone": "01099999999",
  "whatsapp": "01099999999",
  "email": "test@bold.eg"
}

### 9. CUSTOMERS – Set VIP
POST {{base}}/customers/<customer-id>/vip
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "is_vip": true,
  "vip_price_tier": "cost_plus_overhead"
}

### 10. POS – Sale
POST {{base}}/pos/sale
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sync_id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
  "branch_id": "<branch-BOLD-01-id>",
  "customer_phone": "01011111111",
  "payment_method": "cash",
  "language": "ar",
  "items": [
    {
      "variant_id": "<variant-id>",
      "qty": 1
    }
  ]
}

### 11. POS – Return
POST {{base}}/pos/return
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "original_invoice_id": "<sales-invoice-id>",
  "items": [{ "sales_invoice_item_id": "<original-sales-line-id>", "qty": 1 }],
  "reason": "Wrong size"
}

### 12. SALES – PDF Invoice AR
GET {{base}}/sales/<invoice-id>/pdf?lang=ar
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 13. SALES – PDF Invoice EN
GET {{base}}/sales/<invoice-id>/pdf?lang=en
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 14. SUPPLIERS – List
GET {{base}}/suppliers?q=Mohamed
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 15. SUPPLIERS – Create
POST {{base}}/suppliers
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "تاجر اختبار",
  "company_name": "Test Trading Co.",
  "phone": "01299999999",
  "alias_names": ["Test Co", "TTCo"]
}

### 16. SUPPLIERS – Resolve alias (OCR)
GET {{base}}/suppliers/resolve/alias?name=Mohamed%20Fabrics%20Co.
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 17. PURCHASING – List invoices
GET {{base}}/purchasing/invoices?branch_id=<branch-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 18. PURCHASING – Receive stock
POST {{base}}/purchasing/receive
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "supplier_id": "<supplier-id>",
  "branch_id": "<branch-id>",
  "invoice_number": "TEST-001",
  "discount_percent": 5,
  "items": [
    { "variant_id": "<variant-id>", "qty": 50, "unit_cost": 80 }
  ],
  "created_by": "<warehouse-user-id>"
}

### 19. PURCHASING – OCR import
POST {{base}}/purchasing/ocr-import
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fileUrl": "uploads/supplier-invoice-001.pdf"
}

### 20. TRANSFERS – List
GET {{base}}/transfers?branch_id=<branch-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 21. TRANSFERS – Create
POST {{base}}/transfers
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "from_branch_id": "<branch-1-id>",
  "to_branch_id": "<branch-2-id>",
  "created_by": "<manager-user-id>"
}

### 22. TRANSFERS – Ship
POST {{base}}/transfers/<transfer-id>/ship
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 23. TRANSFERS – Receive (with stock movement)
POST {{base}}/transfers/<transfer-id>/receive
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    { "variant_id": "<variant-id>", "qty": 5 }
  ]
}

### 24. REPORTS – Sales
GET {{base}}/reports/sales?from=2026-06-01&to=2026-07-01&branch_id=<branch-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 25. REPORTS – Best sellers
GET {{base}}/reports/best-sellers?branch_id=<branch-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 26. REPORTS – Send Email/WhatsApp
POST {{base}}/reports/send
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "from": "2026-06-01",
  "to": "2026-07-01",
  "channels": ["email", "whatsapp"]
}

### 27. OFFERS – Suggestions
GET {{base}}/offers/suggestions?branch_id=<branch-id>
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 28. OFFERS – Approve/Reject
POST {{base}}/offers/<offer-id>/review
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "approved",
  "reviewed_by": "<owner-user-id>"
}

### 29. BRANCHES – List
GET {{base}}/branches
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 30. USERS – List
GET {{base}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 31. SYNC – Pull (POS offline)
GET {{base}}/sync/pull?branch_id=<branch-id>&since=2026-01-01T00:00:00Z
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 32. SYNC – Push (POS offline)
POST {{base}}/sync/push
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batch": []
}

### End – 32 endpoints traced
### Seed data includes:
### - 12 products, 28 variants, barcodes 6223001000011 …
### - 8 customers – VIP: 01011111111, 01033333333
### - 15 sales invoices, 2 returns
### - Users: +200100000000 … +200100000003 / Bold1234
